# Project ASI — this is a Markdown knowledge repo. Keep it clean.

# OS / filesystem cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# Temp / backup files
*.tmp
*.bak
*.orig

# Local, private notes not meant for the shared history
# (use this prefix for anything you want to keep off GitHub)
LOCAL_*
*.local.md

# Purchased / copyrighted source material — kept LOCAL only, never published.
# You drop bought PDFs/EPUBs here; I read them to write notes; git ignores them.
# (The folder's README is kept tracked so the structure is visible on GitHub.)
RESOURCES/library/*
!RESOURCES/library/README.md
*.pdf
*.epub
*.mobi
*.azw3

# (No build artifacts expected — this repo is plain text by design.)

# 11GB local book/video collection � NEVER commit (a backup copy exists elsewhere)
local_resources/
*.mp4
*.djvu
*.chm

# Corpus � the LOCAL grounding substrate: source text (papers/textbooks/courses)
# extracted to .txt and chunked, used ONLY to write grounded modules. Kept local
# like local_resources/ (redistribution/copyright + size). Only the tracking + plan
# markdown at the corpus ROOT is published, so the structure & status stay visible.
RESOURCES/corpus/papers/**
RESOURCES/corpus/textbooks/**
RESOURCES/corpus/courses/**
!RESOURCES/corpus/papers/.gitkeep
!RESOURCES/corpus/textbooks/.gitkeep
!RESOURCES/corpus/courses/.gitkeep
